@opsx:new create-event-tests
Objective: Create traditional E2E tests using Cypress for the Event Registration screen (`/event/new`).
Location: Create the test file within the generated E2E project (e.g., `apps/frontend-e2e/src/e2e/event-registrations.cy.ts`).

Mandatory guidelines:
1 - Success scenario: Navigate to the `event/new` route, fill in the fields (name, address, capacity, date) using standard CSS selectors (class, id, or name), and click the submit button to ensure successful submission.
2 - Error scenario: Navigate to `event/new`, submit the empty form, and use assertions to verify that native validation error messages appear on the screen.
3 - Golden rule: Use exclusively standard Cypress syntax (`cy.get()`, `cy.contains()`, `should()`). Do not add external AI libraries at this stage.
